  "texts": [
    "The first human instance of monkeypox virus infection involved a nine-month-old baby with smallpox symptoms, which was documented in the Democratic Republic of the Congo (DRC) in 1970.",
    "Between 1970 and 1990, there were over 400 instances of Mpox reported in Africa, with the majority occurring in the Democratic Republic of the Congo (Table 1).",
    "The DRC saw a protracted human monkeypox outbreak in 1996 (Heymann et al., 1998).",
    "Between February 1996 and February 1997, there were about 511 infected patients that underwent evaluation (Ullah et al., 2023).",
    "More than five hundred cases of monkeypox have been reported in 1999."
  ],
